abstract: MANCHESTER, May 1. At a meeting of the Committee of the Spinners' and Manufacturers' Association yesterday a communication from the operatives was received, offering to submit the subject of the reduction of wages to arbitration, but the committee decided to refuse arbitration. It was expressed as certain that unless the strike terminates before next Wednesday the Preston employers will again close their mills.

abstract: OMAHA, May 2. General crop reports from various parts of the State are flattering to the highest degree. abstract: POTTSVILLE, May 9. Two fatal accidents occurred in collieries near this place to-day. The first was at the Gate View Colliery, on the outskirts of Pottsville, and was of a very unusual character. It was shortly before 7 o'clock, and the men were going to work, being lowered down the slope, which is very steep, in mine cars.
